Certainly! To generate a PHP array containing the numbers 145, 156, 400, and 454, sorted in descending order without any repeated elements, you can modify the PHP code as follows:

```php
<?php
$numbers = [145, 156, 400, 454];

// Remove any duplicate elements (if present)
$numbers = array_unique($numbers);

// Sort the array in descending order
rsort($numbers);

// Print the resulting array
print_r($numbers);
?>
```

This code will produce an array that contains the numbers 454, 400, 156, and 145, in descending order without duplicates.
